  "The ground exerts a smaller upward force because it is much more massive": "",
  "The ground exerts a larger upward force to overcome the ball's weight": "",
  "By Newton's Third Law, the ground exerts an equal and opposite force on the ball. The ball pushes down on the ground, and the ground pushes up on the ball with equal magnitude. This upward push is what causes the ball to bounce back up.": "",
  "A student fires a rifle at a shooting range and feels the rifle kick backward against the shoulder. What explains this 'kick' or recoil?": "",
