  "Sound waves from the shot bounce off nearby walls and push the rifle backward": "",
  "The rifle pushes the bullet forward (action), and by Newton's Third Law the bullet pushes the rifle backward (reaction) with equal force. The rifle recoils less violently than the bullet moves because the rifle has much more mass (F = ma).": "",
  "A bird flies by pushing air downward with its wings. According to Newton's Third Law, what happens to the bird?": "",
