  "The nail pushes the board downward instead of pushing the hammer back": "",
  "By Newton's Third Law, the nail pushes back on the hammer with a force equal in magnitude and opposite in direction. This is why the hammer slows down or bounces slightly upon hitting the nail — the nail exerts a reaction force on it.": "",
  "Two ice skaters face each other and push off from one another. Skater A has a mass of 50 kg and Skater B has a mass of 75 kg. Which skater accelerates more?": "",
